FT  07 FEB 92 / UK News (Employment): Europe-wide union mergers forecast
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR BILL JORDAN, president of the AEU engineering union, yesterday predicted
that mergers between unions of different European countries were likely
following the creation of the single market, Michael Smith writes.
Mr Jordan said 1992 had set in motion an unstoppable process. He predicted
that mergers of European unions would happen within his lifetime.
Mr Jordan was speaking before holding talks in Dusseldorf with Mr Franz
Steinkuhler, president of IG Metall, the German manufacturing union. They
were discussing the merger of the AEU and the EETPU electricians' union,
likely to take place within three months, and the relationship between the
merged union and IG Metall.
In a recent campaign to win shorter hours, the UK unions drew lessons from a
similar drive by West German unions in the mid 1980s.
Mr Jordan said he saw the merged union of 1m members working even more
closely with IG Metall. He said: 'Together we will forge a partnership that
will meet and match the growing power of multi-national companies.
'But there is a positive message for Europe's employers; that the aims of
this engineering union alliance are simply the best pay, conditions and
products in the world.'
Letters, Page 13
