<HEADLINE>
FT  07 FEB 92 / World Trade News: Texaco to resume Kuwait output
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Texaco is hoping to resume oil output in Kuwait's Wafra field later this
month, writes Alan Friedman in New York. The company is aiming to produce
around 50,000 barrels a day from Wafra, a level that would be well below the
140,000 bpd before the Iraqi invasion. Oil output from Wafra is shared
equally by Texaco and the state-owned Kuwait Oil Company. The onshore field
lies in a zone along the border between Kuwait and Saudi Arabia.
Before the Gulf war Texaco refined its output from Wafra at the Mina Saudi
refinery. The US company will now be exporting crude directly from Wafra and
analysts suggest that it may seek to sell the high-sulphur oil to Japan.
</TEXT>
