<HEADLINE>
FT  07 FEB 92 / Finns swing in favour of joining EC
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HELSINKI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FINLAND'S President Mauno Koivisto is expected today to add his support to
the growing momentum for an early application to join the European
Community, writes Robert Taylor in Helsinki
This month Prime Minister Esko Aho and his cabinet will decide on an EC
application, and parliament will vote on the issue.
The formal application will be made by mid-March, ensuring that Finland can
join Sweden and Austria in parallel entry negotiations. These could begin
late this year.
The only remaining doubts lie in the attitude of Mr Aho's ruling Centre
Party, which is divided. Many rural supporters fear EC membership will
devastate Finland's highly-protected agriculture. Negotiations on entry
terms on farming may prove difficult.
The swing towards EC entry follows the realisation that a 19-nation European
Economic Area would only be a transitional arrangement, particularly after
Sweden opted in 1990 to seek EC entry.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
