borrowings were reduced by more than Pounds 1.5m; at the 1991 year-end bank
indebtedness was about Pounds 1.4m.
Mr Michael Wheller, chairman and chief executive, said he hoped to put out a
statement shortly. He said that the group needed just Pounds 600,000 of
working capital and that a company doctor, who would have been appointed
executive chairman, had joined the group.
