period a year earlier. Earnings per share emerged at 0.39p (0.07p). The
company intends to pay a final dividend of not less than 0.1p for the
current year to end-May, the first distribution since January 1990.
The improved results reflected better margins and a lower interest charge.
Following a Pounds 2.2m rights issue last July, it has paid off all bank
