FT  06 FEB 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After an uncertain start to this week's Australian wool sales, prices have
moved steadily ahead. Strength is again most apparent in middle and broader
categories. New Zealand wool was also dearer for practically all categories
in the crossbred offering there, by around 5%. After a slow start to the
second half of the selling season demand appears to be picking up and
clearences to the trade have improved. The Australian Wool Corporation's
market indicator reached 585 on February 5, some 4 cents higher than a week
ago, after softening to 576 on February 3.
