is raising at least L78.5bn in new capital. Sasib will issue 15.7m new
savings shares, to be priced at no less than L5,000 each, as part of a
convertible bond issue.
The money will help to improve Sasib's balance sheet after last year's
acquisitions, which contributed to a L54.4bn fall in net liquidity to L68bn
at the end of 1991.
